data.text:
Bryansk

City in Bryansk Oblast, Russia

Distance: Approx. 1120 meters

Latitude and longitude: 53.2425,34.36666667

Bryansk (Russian: Брянск, IPA: [brʲansk]) is a city and the administrative center of Bryansk Oblast, Russia, situated on the River Desna, 379 kilometers (235 mi) southwest of Moscow. It has a population of 379,152 at the 2021 census.

Svensky Monastery

Distance: Approx. 5936 meters

Latitude and longitude: 53.2056,34.3281

Svensky Monastery (Russian: Свенский монастырь) is a Russian Orthodox monastery located at the confluence of the Desna and Sven Rivers, three miles from Bryansk, Russia. The monastery was originally known as Svinsky, after the Svin River, but the spelling was subsequently changed to Svensky, because "svinsky" also means "of the swine" in Russian. Church legends attribute the monastery's foundation to Prince Roman of Bryansk, who was reportedly buried there.

Dynamo Stadium (Bryansk)

Sports venue in Bryansk, Russia

Distance: Approx. 9324 meters

Latitude and longitude: 53.31826389,34.28578889

Dynamo Stadium is a multi-purpose stadium in Bryansk, Russia. It was built in 1924, refitted in 1960 and 2004 years. Stadium is currently used mostly for football matches and is the home ground of FC Dynamo Bryansk.

Bolva

River in Russia

Distance: Approx. 4407 meters

Latitude and longitude: 53.2852,34.3354

The Bolva (Russian: Болва) is a river in Kaluga and Bryansk Oblasts in Russia. It is a left tributary of the Desna. It is 213 km in length, with a drainage basin of 4340 km2.

Bryansky District

District in Bryansk Oblast, Russia

Distance: Approx. 3405 meters

Latitude and longitude: 53.26666667,34.41666667

Bryansky District (Russian: Бря́нский райо́н) is an administrative and municipal district (raion), one of the twenty-seven in Bryansk Oblast, Russia. It is located in the northeast of the oblast. The area of the district is 1,801 square kilometers (695 sq mi).

Bryansk Machine-Building Plant

Heavy industry company in Bryansk, Russia

Distance: Approx. 6124 meters

Latitude and longitude: 53.29980556,34.32588889

Bryansk Machine-Building Plant (Russian: Брянский машиностроительный завод) is a company based in Bryansk, Russia and established in 1873. It is part of Transmashholding. The Bryansk Machine-Building Plant is the oldest builder of transportation equipment in Russia.

Bolshoye Polpino

Urban locality in Bryansk Oblast, Russia

Distance: Approx. 9049 meters

Latitude and longitude: 53.24444444,34.50694444

Bolshoye Polpino (Russian: Большо́е По́лпино) is an urban locality (urban-type settlement) under the administrative jurisdiction of the town of oblast significance of Bryansk of Bryansk Oblast, Russia. Population: 5,859 (2021 Census); 6,356 (2010 Russian census); 4,613 (2002 Census); 6,374 (1989 Soviet census).

Raditsa-Krylovka

Urban locality in Bryansk Oblast, Russia

Distance: Approx. 5338 meters

Latitude and longitude: 53.3,34.36805556

Raditsa-Krylovka (Russian: Ра́дица-Кры́ловка) is an urban locality (urban-type settlement) under the administrative jurisdiction of the town of oblast significance of Bryansk of Bryansk Oblast, Russia. Population: 3,151 (2021 Census); 3,526 (2010 Russian census); 3,513 (2002 Census); 3,818 (1989 Soviet census).
